This paper is primarily focused on the dynamics of gradient descent in learning neural networks for classification problems, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the geometric conditions on the network weights, which is related to the field of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also deals with the classification of data, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of gradient descent, which is a topic in optimization and numerical analysis (cs.SI).
